  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WASH in the most vulnerable communities.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNICEF will respond in Rural Hama, and in Raqqa to the most acute WASH needs with a comprehensive combination of medium-term and immediate life-saving activities including:
1.	Immediate Life-Saving Response: 
	Provision of WASH facilities for IDPs camps

2.	Medium-Term Response:
	Quick repair and rehabilitation of water networks 
	Procurement of spare parts, pipelines, supplies and equipment to maintain existing water and sewerage networks in newly accessible areas
Areas of intervention:

 Rural Hama:
	Rehabilitation of public water networks at Maar Shohur/ Kafer Ra&#x2019;a


Raqqa:
	WASH services required to relocate IDPs from Twahinia settlement to Mahmoudli camp</narrative>
  </description>
